content:
Certainly! Below is a sample HTML page with embedded JavaScript that outlines the rules for your charity marathon and includes a simple script to calculate the time taken by each participant to complete the marathon.

### HTML Page with Marathon Rules

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Charity Marathon Rules</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 20px;
        }
        h1, h2 {
            color: #0044cc;
        }
        ul {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding: 0;
        }
        li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .timer {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Charity Marathon Rules</h1>

    <h2>Registration Details</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Participants must register online through our official website.</li>
        <li>Registration closes one week before the marathon date.</li>
        <li>Entry fee is non-refundable and will be donated to the cause.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Participants must be at least 18 years old.</li>
        <li>All participants must sign a waiver form prior to the event.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Dress Code</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Wear comfortable running attire and sports shoes.</li>
        <li>Participants must wear the official marathon bib at all times.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Prohibited Items</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>No bicycles, rollerblades, or skateboards.</li>
        <li>No pets allowed on the marathon route.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Medical Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Participants should be in good health and consult a physician if necessary.</li>
        <li>Emergency medical teams will be available along the route.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Additional Information</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Water stations will be available at regular intervals.</li>
        <li>Participants should arrive at least 30 minutes before the start.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="timer">
        <h2>Calculate Marathon Time</h2>
        <label for="start-time">Start Time (HH:MM:SS): </label>
        <input type="text" id="start-time" placeholder="e.g., 08:00:00">
        <br><br>
        <label for="end-time">End Time (HH:MM:SS): </label>
        <input type="text" id="end-time" placeholder="e.g., 10:30:00">
        <br><br>
        <button onclick="calculateTime()">Calculate Time Taken</button>
        <p id="result"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        function calculateTime() {
            const startTime = document.getElementById('start-time').value;
            const endTime = document.getElementById('end-time').value;

            if (!startTime || !endTime) {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "Please enter both start and end times.";
                return;
            }

            const start = startTime.split(':').map(Number);
            const end = endTime.split(':').map(Number);

            const startSeconds = start[0] * 3600 + start[1] * 60 + start[2];
            const endSeconds = end[0] * 3600 + end[1] * 60 + end[2];

            if (endSeconds < startSeconds) {
                document.getElementById('result').innerText = "End time must be after start time.";
                return;
            }

            const durationSeconds = endSeconds - startSeconds;
            const hours = Math.floor(durationSeconds / 3600);
            const minutes = Math.floor((durationSeconds % 3600) / 60);
            const seconds = durationSeconds % 60;

            document.getElementById('result').innerText = `Time taken: ${hours}h ${minutes}m ${seconds}s`;
        }
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

- **HTML Structure**: The page includes sections for registration details, eligibility criteria, dress code, prohibited items, medical requirements, and additional information. Each section is clearly defined with headings and lists.

- **JavaScript Timer**: The script allows users to input the start and end times of their marathon run. It calculates the time taken by converting the time into seconds, computing the difference, and then converting it back into hours, minutes, and seconds.

- **Styling**: Basic CSS styling is applied for readability and a clean layout. You can further enhance the design as needed.

You can customize the content, style, and functionality according to your specific requirements.
